s: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">609</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":609,\"repo\":\"BubuAnabelas/awesome-markdown\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--></li>","updatedAt":"2021-08-25T20:26:40.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Other Lists</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://codeberg.org/teaserbot-labs/delightful-open-science\">Delightful Open Science</a></li>","updatedAt":"2021-08-25T20:26:40.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Converters and Filters</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://myst-parser.readthedocs.io/en/latest/\">MyST</a> - Markedly Structured Text,\na superset of CommonMark markdown with reStructuredText like features.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-29T16:26:15.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Templates</h2><h3>Articles</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/davecap/markdown-latex-boilerplate/#readme\">Pandoc Markdown-LaTeX\nBoilerplate</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/davecap/markdown-latex-boilerplate/#readme\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">93</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":93,\"repo\":\"davecap/markdown-latex-boilerplate\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Demonstrate\nhow to integrate Pandoc with an existing LaTeX template which\nrequires some boilerplate code (i.e. LaTeX preamble), thus avoiding the\n<code>latexmk</code> dependency.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-24T15:16:30.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Bibliography</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://editor.citationstyles.org/\">Citation Style Language (CSL) styles</a> - Crowdsourced\nrepository with over 9000 free CSL citation styles and an online\neditor to create new ones.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-29T10:03:13.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Converters and Filters</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://pandoc.org/MANUAL\">pandoc</a> - Haskell library for converting from\none markup format to another, and a command-line tool that uses this\nlibrary 🔖 🔗.\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/smathot/academicmarkdown#readme\">Academic Markdown</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/smathot/academicmarkdown#readme\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">334</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":334,\"repo\":\"smathot/academicmarkdown\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Python wrapper over Pandoc with specialized extensions to parse certain\nelements, making it a superset of Pandoc Markdown flavour 🔖\n🔗.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/jgm/pandoc/wiki/Pandoc-Filters\">Pandoc filters</a> - List of\naddons to pandoc which implement extra features such as citations and\ncross-references.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://scorreia.com/software/panflute/\">Panflute</a> - Pythonic alternative\nto John MacFarlane's pandocfilters.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-29T09:09:56.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Templates</h2><h3>Books</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/Wandmalfarbe/pandoc-latex-template\">Eisvogel</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/Wandmalfarbe/pandoc-latex-template\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">4.5k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":4549,\"repo\":\"Wandmalfarbe/pandoc-latex-template\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Clean academic pandoc LaTeX template.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-29T09:09:56.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Tutorials</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://u.arizona.edu/~selisker/post/workflow/\">Scott Selisker</a> - Plain Text Workflow for Academic Writing with Atom.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-29T09:09:56.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Bibliography</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://zbib.org/\">ZoteroBib</a> - Online bibliography reference manager.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-29T08:23:27.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Spell Checking and Linting</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://aspell.net/\">GNU Aspell</a> - Command line spell checker.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-08T11:09:56.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Spell Checking and Linting</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://hunspell.github.io/\">Hunspell</a> - Command line spell checker.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-08T11:09:56.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Word Processors</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://atom.io\">Atom</a> - Popular IDE with Markdown support.\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/shd101wyy/markdown-preview-enhanced\">Markdown Preview Enhanced for Atom</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/shd101wyy/markdown-preview-enhanced\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margi