_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":387,\"repo\":\"vim-pandoc/vim-pandoc-syntax\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Pandoc syntax highlighting for Vim.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-07T20:49:41.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Word Processors</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://code.visualstudio.com/\">Visual Studio Code</a> - Popular IDE with Markdown support.\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/yzhang-gh/vscode-markdown/#readme\">Markdown All in One</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/yzhang-gh/vscode-markdown/#readme\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">2.4k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":2400,\"repo\":\"yzhang-gh/vscode-markdown\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Extension for enhanced\nMarkdown support in VSCode, such as preview and auto completion to name a few.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-07T20:49:41.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Word Processors</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.zettlr.com/\">Zettlr</a> - Markdown editor which\nintegrates CSL, BibLaTeX, Pandoc and many other tools\n🔖 🔗.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-07T20:49:41.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Bibliography</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.jabref.org/\">JabRef</a> - Open source bibliography reference manager.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-07T20:49:41.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Bibliography</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.zotero.org/\">Zotero</a> - FOSS tool to collect, organize, cite, and\nshare research.\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://retorque.re/zotero-better-bibtex/\">Better BibTeX for Zotero</a> - Enhanced\nBibTeX / BibLaTeX integration for Zotero.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://zotfile.com/\">ZotFile for Zotero</a> - Enhanced PDF file management for Zotero.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-07T20:49:41.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Illustrations</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.diagrams.net/\">diagrams.net</a> - Open source, online, desktop and\ncontainer deployable diagramming software.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-07T20:49:41.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Illustrations</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://graphviz.org/\">graphviz</a> - Visualization software for graphs and\nnetworks which uses a domain-specific DOT language.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-07T20:49:41.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Illustrations</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://mermaid-js.github.io/mermaid-live-editor/\">Mermaid Live Editor</a> - Define simple diagrams instead of drawing them.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-07T20:49:41.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Illustrations</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://vega.github.io/vega-lite/examples/\">Vega Lite</a> - Define charts and more complex diagrams.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-07T20:49:41.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Illustrations</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://plantuml.com/\">PlantUML</a> - Define UML diagrams instead of drawing them.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-07T20:49:41.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Templates</h2><h3>Articles</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/svmiller/svm-r-markdown-templates/\">Steve's R Markdown Templates</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/svmiller/svm-r-markdown-templates/\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">814</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":814,\"repo\":\"svmiller/svm-r-markdown-templates\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Academic manuscript, memos, Beamer presentation, syllabus and CV.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-07T20:49:41.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Tutorials</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://programminghistorian.org/en/lessons/sustainable-authorship-in-plain-text-using-pandoc-and-markdown\">Dennis Tenen and Grant Wythoff</a> - Sustainable Authorship in Plain Text using Pandoc and Markdown.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-07T20:49:41.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Templates</h2><h3>Articles</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/JensErat/scientific-markdown/#readme\">scientific-markdown</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/JensErat/scientific-markdown/#readme\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">39</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":39,\"repo\":\"JensErat/scientific-markdown\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Example\nfor use of Markdown for scientific publications using Pandoc and\n<code>latexmk</code>.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-07T16:27:21.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Templates</h2><h3>Presentations</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/jez/pandoc-starter/#readme\">pandoc-starter</a><a data-role=\"trackawe